<body><div><span><strong>Article Title:</strong> </span><span>6 Best Music Mixes for Massages</span></div><br />
<div><span><strong>Article Content: </strong></span><br /><span><p>Relaxing music is an essential component of a good massage because it puts your customer in the right mindset. You have to carefully select relaxing music to create the best massage experience possible. Of course, you should also ask your customers if they have a music preference, but also know what works for a massage and what doesn’t. So, take a look at this list of popular music for massages for CDs to play in their entirety or you can make a great massage mix of your own.</p>
<h2><strong><em>Music for Healing</em> by Steven Halpren</strong></h2>
<p><strong><img src="http://farm5.staticflickr.com/4152/4950986271_c5c19c7a1a.jpg" alt="" width="500" height="375" /><br /></strong></p>
<p>Image via <a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/o5com/4950986271/">Flickr</a> by o5com<strong><br /><br /></strong></p>
<p>Steven Halpren is a master of New Age music, and he is even known in the music community as a healing expert. His CD, <em>Music for Healing</em>, is very relaxing and enchanting, but it also offers a unique sound that gives customers a slightly different experience than they are used to. Another relaxing CD from Stephen Halpren is <em>Music for Massage</em>.</p>
<h2></h2>
<h2><strong><em>Blade Runner</em> by Vangelis</strong></h2>
<p><img title="Blade Runner by Vangelis" src="http://farm1.staticflickr.com/133/359880203_cbe95024e2.jpg" alt="Blade Runner by Vangelis" width="485" height="500" /></p>
<p>Image via <a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/luxuryluke/359880203/" target="_blank">Flickr</a> by luxuryluke</p>
<p>Vangelis is a Greek composer that creates instrumental music that is often featured in films. He began playing the piano at four and started performing publicly at six. So, he has dedicated his life to creating music that touches people’s souls. He is most popular for his contribution, <em>Chariots of Fire</em>. Actually, the entire <em>Blade Runner</em> CD is a great soundtrack to play during a massage.</p>
<h2><strong><em>And Winter Came</em> by Enya</strong></h2>
<p><strong><img title="And Winter Came by Enya" src="http://farm4.staticflickr.com/3040/3102559080_abe2d1509e.jpg" alt="And Winter Came by Enya" width="400" height="402" /></strong></p>
<p>Image via <a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/15526636@N04/3102559080/" target="_blank">Flickr</a> by maartinoo<strong><br /></strong></p>
<p>Enya is one of the world’s best known female artists for relaxing music. She has sold more than 60 million albums across the globe and been nominated for five Grammy Awards. Her music is even popular on the radio. You can’t go wrong playing Enya during a massage unless your customer wants something they’ve never heard before. <em>And Winter Came</em> is a great CD for a massage, but other CDs from Enya include, <em>Don’t Paint the Sky with Stars</em>, <em>Orinoco Flow</em>, and <em>Shepherd Moons</em>.</p>
<h2><strong><em>No Blue Thing</em> by Ray Lynch</strong></h2>
<p><strong><br /><img src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/f/fc/Raylynchphoto.jpg" alt="" width="390" height="499" /><br /></strong></p>
<p><strong> </strong>Image via <a href="http://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Raylynchphoto.jpg">Wikimedia</a></p>
<p>Music by Ray Lynch features acoustic and electronic sounds that are presented in a classical way. He is also good at experimenting with unconventional sounds and embracing new musical technologies. His music is a great for background music during and energizing massage that soothes the body and soul.</p>
<h2><strong><em>Music for Airports</em> by Brian Eno</strong></h2>
<p><img title="Music for Airports" src="http://farm4.staticflickr.com/3029/2554970970_61dfea0400.jpg" alt="Music for Airports" width="500" height="493" /></p>
<p>Image via <a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/exquisitur/2554970970/" target="_blank">Flickr</a> by exquisitur</p>
<p>Brian Eno has a couple different music albums featuring relaxing music. His music is typically characterized as ambient or instrumental, which is perfect for setting the mood of a massage. In addition to his ambient CD mixes, Brian Eno has contributed music to U2, David Bowie, and several television programs and commercials. He definitely knows how to appeal to people’s emotions with his music.</p>
<h2><strong><em>The Celtic Book of Days</em> by David Arkenstone</strong></h2>
<p><strong><img src="http://farm4.staticflickr.com/3547/3339318085_c1c417beb4.jpg" alt="" width="500" height="334" /><br /></strong></p>
<p>Image via <a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/stevendepolo/3339318085/">Flickr</a> by stevendepolo<strong><br /><br /></strong></p>
<p>This New Age music artist uses technology to engineer a sound that combines rock influences with relaxing sounds. David Arkenstone was nominated for two Grammy Awards and some of his songs have been on the Billboard smash hits list. Some of his other albums include, <em>Spirit of the Rainforest</em>, and <em>Caravan of Light</em>.</p>
<p>All of the CD mixes mentioned here are a great place to start your massage music collection, but it is by no means a complete list. Are there any other music artists or CD mixes that you love using for your massages?</p>
